ExecDesc.value: Adobe Flash Player MP4 Sequence Parameter Set Parsing Buffer Overflow(IPV6 Version)

EngDesc.value: A stack buffer overflow exists in Adobe Flash Player. The issue can manifest itself when it parses the Sequence Parameter Set structure in an MP4 file. An attacker could exploit this vulnerability by enticing a target user to visit a specially crafted web page. A successful attack leveraging this vulnerability could lead to arbitrary code execution on the vulnerable system in the security context of the affected application.
